 ## Language Requirements

- **User Interface Language**: Korean (한국어)
  - All visible text in the UI must be in Korean
  - This includes:
    - Menu items
    - Button labels
    - Form labels and placeholders
    - Error messages
    - Headers and titles
    - Any other user-facing text

- **Code Comments/Documentation**:
  - Code comments can be in English for developer clarity
  - Variable names should be in English for standard coding practices
  - Internal documentation can be in English

- **Translation Process**:
  - When adapting components from English sources, ensure all user-visible text is translated to Korean
  - Maintain proper Korean grammar and natural expressions
  - Consider Korean language text length in UI design (may differ from English)

- **Example**:
  ```tsx
  // ✅ DO: Translate user-facing content
  <Button variant="ghost" className="w-full justify-start" asChild>
    <Link href="/products">
      <Icon className="mr-2 h-4 w-4" />
      상품
    </Link>
  </Button>

  // ❌ DON'T: Keep English in the UI
  <Button variant="ghost" className="w-full justify-start" asChild>
    <Link href="/products">
      <Icon className="mr-2 h-4 w-4" />
      Products
    </Link>
  </Button>
  ``` 